import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['US_Gross', 'Worldwide_Gross']]
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='US_Gross', y='Worldwide_Gross')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Production_Budget', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["Production_Budget"].median():,.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Production Budget')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(data=data[['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating']], palette="Set3")
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Rating Type')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rating')
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Rotten Tomatoes', 'IMDB'])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="MPAA_Rating", data=data, palette="Set2")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.axhline(y=data['MPAA_Rating'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
